content: I keep getting this.. tried a bunch of different links and clearing my cache. Any ideas or should I just keep trying?
<@936622618293968958> did it refresh once you backed out and clicked again? We just switched to WI, so that might have caused the glitch?
Nope. I'll just keep trying.  Maybe network is shaky in my area. Thanks Jen!

<@936622618293968958> you may want to close out completely, toggle your internet connection off, wait a few minutes, toggle internet back on, then reconnect to the dialer. Which I know is basically a fancy way of saying...have you tried unplugging it and plugging it back in again. But actually disconnecting from my internet network and reconnecting has helped in certain situations.
I haven't tried a hard reset like that, but will give it a go. Appreciate it!!
Sorry, I know this is frustrating. 2 things to try - first if you're on a Safari browser, try Chrome. second, see if going inconito fixes it.
Thanks, Larry! I'll give that a go, cause I was still getting the error. Hopefully it's just me and not a bunch of callers.
